<TITLE> Ctg BNP leaders called to Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Nov 17 (bdnews24.com)  BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain has summoned the party's Chittagong leaders to Dhaka following the clashes that broke up the metropolitan unit's long awaited council. The meeting with Delwar is scheduled for Wednesday, Amir Khasru Mahmud Chowdhury, convenor of BNP's Chittagong metropolitan unit, told bdnews24.com Tuesday. A series of clashes fuelled by internal squabbling foiled the Chittagong council, attempted after a hiatus of 20 years on Monday. Supporters of BNP joint secretary general Abdullah Al Noman and Amir Khasru blamed each other for the untoward occurrences at the Institute of Engineers, Chittagong, where the scheduled council dissolved in chaos as the two factions faced off. Amir Khasru told bdnews24.com on Tuesday, "We're being called to a meeting with the secretary general to determine what should be done." The leaders summoned from Chittagong are Amir Khasru, Noman, joint convenors of Chittagong city unit Dastagir Chowdhury, Ershad Ullah and Shamsul Alam. Central leaders, who were in Chittagong for the council, BNP vice chairman M Morshed Khan and international secretary Mir Mohammad Nasir Uddin, have also been asked to the meeting All were in the city by Tuesday afternoon. bd
